erty and operations.In the Edo period, a practice known as "dual pilgrimage" emerged, encouraging worshippers to visit both {{ill|Yuga Daigongen|ja|瑜伽大権現|en}} and {{ill|Konpira Gongen|en}} in {{ill|Sanuki Province|ja|讃岐国|en}}.== Deities ==The shrine enshrines Hikosa no Oshinomikoto, Kamunaobi-no-Kami, Daigongen (Honji Buddha: {{ill|Amitābha|ja|阿弥陀如来}}, {{ill|Yakushi Nyorai|ja|薬師如来}}), and others, including:* {{ill|Hikosa-no-Oshinomikoto|ja|彦狭知命}}* {{ill|Kamunaobi-no-Kami|ja|神直日神}}* {{ill|Yuga Daigongen|ja|瑜伽大権現|en}} (associated Buddhas: {{ill|Amitābha|ja|阿弥陀如来}}, {{ill|Yakushi Nyorai|ja|薬師如来}})* {{ill|Teokihobufu no Mikoto|ja|手置帆負命}} * {{ill|Amenominakanushi|ja|天之御中主神}}* {{ill|Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|素盞鳴命}}* {{ill|Ukanomitama|lt=Ukanomitama-no-Kami|ja|倉稲魂命}}* {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|菅原道真}}* {{ill|Watatsumi|lt=Watatsumi-no-Mikoto|ja|大綿津見命}}*== Cultural Properties ==* '''main hall''' – Built in the early Edo period, it is designated as an {{ill|Important Cultural Property of Okayama Prefecture|ja|岡山県指定重要文化財}} (1961).<ref name=岡山県文>{{Cite web|url=http://www.pref.okayama.jp/cgi-bin/bunka/culture/controller/client/resultDetail.cgi?id=174 |title=main hall of Yuga Shrine |publisher=Okayama Prefecture |accessdate=2018-06-24}}</ref>== Access ==* '''By Car:''' About 15 minutes from ]][[Seto-Chuo Expressway]]'s {{ill|Mizushima Interchange|en}}.* '''By Taxi:''' About 15 minutes from {{ill|Kojima Station|en}} on the {{ill|Seto-Ohashi Line|en}}.* '''By Bus:''' A limited {{ill|Shimoden Bus|en}} service runs from Kojima Station to Yuga Shrine (twice daily). However, buses do not operate on weekends, holidays, or during the New Year period.== References =={{reflist}}== Further Reading ==* Okayama Prefectural High School Social Studies Department History Section, ''Revised Edition: History Walks in Okayama Prefecture,'' Yamakawa Publishing, 1991, pp. 96–97.* On-site informational plaques.== Related Articles ==* {{ill|Rendaiji (Kurashiki)|en}}* {{ill|Kumano Sanzan|en}}* {{ill|Kumano Shrine (Kurashiki)|en}}* {{ill|Kotohira-gū|en}}== External Links ==* [https://yugasan.or.jp/ Yuga Shrine Hongū Official Website]]][[Category:Shinto shrines in Okayama Prefecture]]]][[Category:Ken-sha]]]][[Category:Tandoku shrines]]]][[Category:Yuga faith]]]][[Category:Unsorted completion categories]]
